  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dbb\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dcf\u0daf? \u0d85\u0daf \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd4\u0dba\u0db8 \u0d9a\u0da7\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a \u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0ddc\u0da7\u0dd4\u0db4\u0dc5\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dca\u0da7 \u0db8\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0daf \u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dab\u0dda ?",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Did Basil leave the country? What happened to Basil at Katunayake airport this morning?",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Immigration officials have been away from duty at the \"Silk Route\" passenger clearance terminal where dignitaries can book their flights after paying money in the Katunayake Bandaranaike International Airport since 12.00 am today (July 12).",
        "KAAS Kanugala, President of the Sri Lanka Immigration Department Officers Association, said that he has decided to withdraw from its services until further notice.",
        "It is reported that when former Finance Minister Basil Rajapaksa arrived at Katunayake Airport early this morning (12), he had to turn back from the airport due to strong opposition from passengers and other parties.",
        "The immigration officials said that they did not provide services to the former finance minister Basil Rajapaksa and others to leave the Seda Mawatha terminal.",
        "He further stated that considering the current unstable and crisis situation in Sri Lanka and because there is a possibility of using this Silk Road Clearing Terminal to leave the country in large numbers, accused former political elites have taken steps to withdraw from its services.",
        "Earlier, during the hartal season held in Sri Lanka from June 06 to June 20, the Sri Lankan Immigration and Emigration Departments in the Special Guest Room (V.I.P.Lounge) and Silk Route (Silk Route) in Katunayake Bandaranaike International Airport. Officers had moved to stay away.",
        "Although the BBC tried several times to contact the former Minister Basil Rajapaksa by phone to inquire about this incident, it was unsuccessful.",
        "However, a spokesman for the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna, who did not wish to be named, confirmed to the BBC Sinhala Service during our inquiry this morning that the incident was true.",
        "Meanwhile, the air passengers who were waiting at the passenger terminal of Katunayake Airport at that moment have given warm responses regarding this incident and are currently circulating through social media."
      ],
